<subSubSection id="062A4361A3B7D6D3BB60F389A384FEB8" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7282902AE24ED1EF9687CD3FC53103FD" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6AF7C41DF2F30E113DCDF3E0FCCA2C71" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
(Figure 
<figureCitation id="1D67130BF952CFDE3E465FAD0F018E1F" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution map of Solanum michaelis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.74.10159.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/110010" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">2</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Bolivia in the Departments of Tarija and Santa Cruz; although the species is to be expected in adjacent Paraguay. 
<taxonomicName id="2A66E3B11ED41344692CBC9B93415C58" authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; S. Knapp" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum michaelis" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michaelis">
<emphasis id="2FC49C3CF7168A663E665DC9E3680AA7" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Solanum michaelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in dry Chaco vegetation and in lower inter-Andean valleys, along slopes in sandy soils in mostly unshaded dry creek beds on bare soil, often in areas 
<pageBreakToken id="9E6D630BFD2C98B1F2E8DEAEB7572AA5" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" start="start">that</pageBreakToken>
have been burned, or in more humid Chaco vegetation at the edge of 
<normalizedToken id="13FA0D733A112A6E025FC4C7AF93E4C2" originalValue="“palmares”">&quot;palmares&quot;</normalizedToken>
(stands of 
<taxonomicName id="A969D604A1E363B7A39F43D03225C321" authorityName="Morong" authorityYear="1893" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Copernicia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Copernicia alba" order="Arecales" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="E77B0D77D76A75B59375120CDC7D3EC0" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Copernicia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Morong) between 300-900 m elevation.
</paragraph>
